Description:
1) product: The inventory system. Includes fields such as name,
description, price, and category. Represents the product entity in the MongoDB.
2)promotion: name, description, start and end dates, discount percentage,
and a reference to the associated product. Represents the promotion entity in the MongoDB database.
  3)order: detailing the user, products with quantities, total cost, order status, 
and payment method. Captures the order entity in the MongoDB database.
  4)user: name, email, role, and password. Represents the user entity in the MongoDB database.
  5)inventory: specifying the product and its quantity. Captures the stock information
    for products and their quantities in the MongoDB database.
